sections.content:
The head of every institution shall prepare an annual report for each calendar year on the operation of this Act in respect of the institution.

The annual report must specify:
(a) the number of requests for access to records received;
(b) the number of requests that were granted in whole or in part;
(c) the number of requests that were denied in whole or in part;
(d) the number of requests that were abandoned;
(e) the number of thefts, losses or unauthorized uses or disclosures of personal information reported to the Commissioner during the year;
(f) other prescribed information.

An institution shall assess the following before collecting personal information:
(a) whether the collection is necessary;
(b) the risks associated with the collection, including the risk of harm to an individual;
(c) whether there are less privacy-invasive alternatives.

The head of an institution shall implement steps to prevent or reduce the likelihood of a theft, loss or unauthorized use or disclosure of personal information and to mitigate the risks to individuals in the event of such an occurrence.

Assessments must be updated before making any significant change to the purpose for which personal information is used or disclosed.

The head of an institution shall not use personal information in its custody or under its control except:
(a) where the person to whom the information relates has identified that information in particular and consented to its use;
(b) for the purpose for which it was obtained or compiled or for a consistent purpose;
(c) for the purpose of complying with an Act of the Legislature or an Act of Parliament, a treaty, agreement or arrangement made under such an Act, or a subpoena, warrant or order issued or made by a court, person or body with jurisdiction to compel the production of information;
(d) where the use of the information is permitted by this Act.

The head of an institution shall not disclose personal information in its custody or under its control except:
(a) in accordance with Part I (Access to Information);
(b) where the person to whom the information relates has identified that information in particular and consented to its disclosure;
(c) for the purpose for which it was obtained or compiled or for a consistent purpose;
(d) where disclosure is made to an officer or employee of the institution who needs the record in the performance of their duties;
(e) for the purpose of complying with an Act of the Legislature or an Act of Parliament, a treaty, agreement or arrangement made under such an Act, or a subpoena, warrant or order issued or made by a court, person or body with jurisdiction to compel the production of information;
(f) to a law enforcement agency in Canada to aid an investigation;
(g) in compelling circumstances affecting the health or safety of any individual if upon disclosure notification thereof is mailed to the last known address of the individual to whom the information relates;
(h) for the purpose of a proceeding before a court, tribunal or other entity imposing legal obligations;
(i) where the Commissioner has authorized a research program.
